  "summary": "Malicious code in @asavie/i18n (npm)",
  "details": "On installation the package runs a preinstall hook that fingerprints the host, collecting the hostname and username via os.hostname() and os.userInfo(), and exfiltrates them through both DNS and HTTPS beacons to an out-of-band collaborator listener at oast[.]me. This is a dependency-confusion supply-chain payload that executes automatically during npm install.",
